"""Template for _tell_scan_denylist.py — copy to _tell_scan_denylist.py (gitignored)
and fill in your own project's sensitive literals. Do NOT commit the populated file.

check_tell_scan.py imports SENSITIVE_PATTERNS from _tell_scan_denylist.py at runtime
if present, and falls back to the committed script's generic secrets/PII/IP-range
coverage if the sidecar is absent — so this file being missing degrades coverage
rather than breaking the guard.

Common categories a project might add here: internal tracker-ID prefixes, internal
tooling/doc-path references, internal project-cadence or phase-numbering shorthand,
personal names/usernames, or internal codenames — none of these belong in the
committed script since they are project-specific, not generic secret shapes.
"""

